<HEADER>
A8941 &Cx1f; tic-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BBN-DBACKS-NOTEBOOK-A     06-15 0498
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-DBACKS-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TELEMACO TO GET HIS 1ST START IN ST. LOUIS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By DON KETCHUM AND BOB COHN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - Right-hander  &UR; Amaury Telemaco, who pitched a scoreless
eighth inning on Sunday, will get his first start of the season on
Saturday when the Diamondbacks face the Cardinals in St. Louis.
</P>
<P>
   Telemaco, acquired on waivers from the Chicago Cubs on May 15,
has appeared in nine games for Arizona and has given up three
earned runs on 12 hits in 16 innings. He is getting his chance
because right-hander &UR; Bob Wolcott recently was sent to Triple-A
Tucson. Wolcott made two starts for the Diamondbacks. &QL; 
 &QL; 
White misses game &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Center fielder  &UR; Devon White missed a second straight game Sunday
because of a strained right wrist. He was available for
pinch-running and defense, said Manager &UR; Buck Showalter, who added
that he expects to have White back in the lineup when the
Diamondbacks open a series in Cincinnati against the Reds on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Cool breeze in park &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Do you wonder why they closed the roof at Bank One Ballpark,
even though it doesn't seem that hot outside? The first-pitch
temperature for Saturday's game was 84 degrees. The roof was opened
shortly after the game ended, and the temperature in the lower
seats eventually reached 110.
</P>
<P>
   With the roof closed and the outfield panels open on Sunday, a
cool breeze could be felt throughout the ballpark. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Fabregas: Not quite &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Catcher &UR; Jorge Fabregas, eligible to come off the disabled list
on Tuesday after injuring his right ankle, likely will be sidelined
for another week or so.
</P>
<P>
   Showalter said Fabregas could be activated later in the team's
eight-game trip, but a more likely scenario has him back on the
roster when the Diamondbacks return home on June 24 against Texas.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's frustrating,'' Fabregas said. ``I get up every morning
and say, `Today's going to be the day.' I even use the whirlpool at
my (apartment) complex for extra treatment. I have a long list of
exercises. Then I step on it and it's still not quite right. I'm
trying to be patient, remain positive.''
</P>
<P>
   With the team out of town, Fabregas will return to the minor
league complex in Tucson, where the majority of the team's
rehabilitation is done. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Garcia makes nice catch &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   With White sitting out the game,  &UR; Karim Garcia made his first
start of the season in center field. In the fifth inning, he made a
nice catch on  &UR; Tom Pagnozzi's deep fly ball, then uncorked a
terrific throw to third, narrowly missing  &UR; Royce Clayton, who had
tagged up.
</P>
<P>
   Another new face _ relatively new, anyway _ was  &UR; Brent Brede,
who started in right field. Brede's role has been reduced since
Garcia's call-up from Tucson two weeks ago, and he had been
relegated to pinch-hitting duties. Both bat left-handed. Brede
doubled in three at-bats and made a diving catch and started a
double play on Clayton's line drive in the eighth. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
