<HEADLINE>
BONHAM CARTER SOARS; BUSEY CRASHES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES:  &UR; ``The Wings of the Dove'' &LR;  _ Helena Bonham Carter
stars in this remarkable adaptation of Henry James's novel. She
injects her Jamesian character with blood and fury and sex _
characteristics often lost in other film interpretations.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``The Rage'' &LR;  _ Gary Busey, who started so promisingly in films
such as ``Carny'' and ``The Buddy Holly Story,'' hits rock bottom
in this action-oriented melodrama. As an FBI agent, Busey is beyond
the pale, and he's not given much help from the script. One great
car crash does not a movie make.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Switchback''  &LR; _ Dennis Quaid, whose sense of humor has
softened some pretty bad roles, is dead serious as an FBI agent
searching for a serial killer. The convoluted script betrays its
own sense of logic. The only interesting element is Danny Glover's
chilling performance.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THE CHAIRMAN OF THE BOARD: Frank Sinatra, the actor, has 19
movies available on home video. But he also has several concerts
and performances, including ``Frank Sinatra: Portrait of an
Album,'' ``Frank Sinatra: The Man and His Music with the Count
Basie Orchestra,'' ``Frank Sinatra: A Man and His Music,'' ``Frank
Sinatra in Concert at Royal Festival Hall,'' ``Sinatra: The Main
Event'' and ``Frank Sinatra: Ol' Blue Eyes is Back.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
