<SLUG> BC-FEATURE-BUDGET-ART-BOS </SLUG>
  
 ART ADV.: Photos with HIGHTECH-OLDER and SCI-HEARTS-EXPERIMENTAL
are being transmitted to NYT Photo Service subscribers.  
 For Immediate Release  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following FEATURE stories for
use by NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-DRAFT (Moscow) -- June's the month when thousands of
young Russian men go on the lam, fleeing the draft. Hot on their
tails are burly press gangs that will do anyhing to haul'em in. By
David Filipov. 1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SOUTH-HOCKEY (Washington) -- They're playing the Stanley Cup in
the nation's capital, but that doesn't mean people in this Southern
swamp town know much about pucks. Red tape, they understand. Red
lines? Well, no. By David M. Shribman. 1100 words. (w and s coding)
</P>
<P>
   OLIPHANT-COLUMN (Washington) _ The times are right for a
rejuvenated Peace Corps. By Thomas Oliphant. (w and k coding.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SOUTHERN-BAPTISTS (Undated) -- Since 1979, when conservatives
took over leadership of the nation's largest Protestant
denomination, the southern Baptists have leaned on the Bible to
emerge as a powerful counterweight to mainstream American culture.
By Diego Ribadeneira. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   FBI-IMAGE (Boston) -- The ongoing disclosures of the Boston
FBI's onetime close ties with mobsters is damaging the agency the
way Ruby Ridge and Waco did nationally. By Matthew Brelis. (2
takes)
</P>
<P>
   SKATEBOARD-GIRL (Orange, Calif.) _ Skateboarder Carabeth
Burnside is big business. She's selling acceptance in a sport where
female role models remain almost as rare as when she was a girl. By
Lynda Gorov. 1250 words. (a and s coding)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SMITH-COLUMN (Undated) _ Patricia Smith is not writing today.
</P>
<P>
