<P>
   EXTREME SPORTS RULE!
</P>
<P>
   -------------------
</P>
<P>
   So say the athletes participating in the fourth annual Summer X
Games, which open Friday, June 19, at San Diego's Mariner's Point.
For 10 days, in-line skaters and barefoot water-ski jumpers will
flail through the air. Street lugeing and bicycle stunt riding will
be front and center!
</P>
<P>
   To help you cover this sports event, The New York Times
Syndicate is offering for one-shot purchase an article titled
``EXTREME ATHLETES ARE GOING FROM RADICAL TO RICH'' by Bill
Donahue. In it, Donahue, who has contributed articles to The New
York Times Magazine, George and Outside, reports on the inception
of the X Games, the growing popularity of its radical sporting
events and the role ESPN plays in the games' recognition.
</P>
