<P>
   ALASKA -- TOBACCO. A proposed $1.10 increase in the federal tax
on a pack of cigarettes contained in the Senate tobacco bill would
hit Alaska smokers hard, because they already pay a higher tax than
any other state. But Alaska lawmakers and state health officials
are split over whether it will really cut down on smoking in
Alaska. (Working.) Gorman
</P>
<P>
   GEORGIA -- MONEY. U.S. Rep. Charlie Norwood isn't the richest
member of the Augusta-Aiken congressional delegation, but he's a
good bet to come in second. Williams
</P>
<P>
   INDIANA -- TEACHER. Union Mills kindergarten teacher Peggy
Taylor, who uses apples and pumpkins to teach math to 4-year-olds,
was honored Monday in Washington for her innovative teaching
methods. Thakkar
</P>
<P>
   LOUISIANA -- SCHOLAR. Melissa Mata, high school senior from
Cade, was honored in the nation's capital as a presidential scholar
Monday. Egbert
</P>
<P>
   MARYLAND -- DEF. Working on project. Biers
</P>
<P>
   NEVADA -- TEACH. Two Nevada elementary school teachers were
presented with presidential commendations Monday for their efforts
to promote math and science in the classroom. Preston
</P>
<P>
   -- MAPES. Reno's Mapes Hotel &AMP; Casino was placed on the 11 Most
Endangered Historic Places list Monday by the National Trust for
Historic Preservation. However, the hotel might be saved and turned
into a joint time-share and commercial complex. (Possible.) Preston
</P>
<P>
   OHIO -- AMBULANCES-HOBSON. The U.S. Department of Health and
Human Services has given its blessing to a 26-year-old practice
among Miami Valley hospitals of restocking ambulances. Rep. David
Hobson, R-Springfield, pushed for HHS to drop a new policy of
fining hospitals for this practice. Brown
</P>
<P>
   -- HOBSON-DISCLOSURE. Financial disclosure reports show that
Rep. David Hobson, R-Springfield, listed 51 assets, in addition to
his congressional salary. Eckstein
</P>
<P>
   -- NEWARK. Looking into the revitalization of a city: What
federal resources are available? What have other cities done?
Herard and Barton
</P>
<P>
   -- NEY. A look at the personal financial disclosure of U.S. Rep.
Bob Ney, R-St. Clairesville. Egbert
</P>
<P>
   -- RENT. Low-income Cleveland residents are suffering from a
lack of affordable rental housing, according to a new report.
Egbert
</P>
<P>
   WISCONSIN -- TIBET. Feingold spoke today at the Capitol Hill
rally to free Tibet. Mewborn
