   SUNBEAM _ Sunbeam Corp. chairman Albert Dunlap, nicknamed
``Chain Saw'' as the king of corporate job cutters, now knows what
it's like to be on the receiving end of a pink slip. Sunbeam's
board unanimously voted to remove the supercharged Dunlap after the
home product maker's stock sank, sales lagged and confidence
disappeared. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   DUNLAP _ Board of Directors of Sunbeam fires Albert ``Chainsaw
Dunlap. (Waresh, Palm Beach Post) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   NETWATCH _ATLANTA _ Beware of e-mail letters from celebrities.
Unless they are personal friends of yours, chances are they want
something. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CYBERSCENE _ ATLANTA _ There's something a little silly about
turning to your PC for advice about exercise. After all, if you
didn't spend so danged much time sitting at the keyboard, cruising
the Web and sending e-mail, you'd get outside more. But since the
PC and the Internet are facts of life now, you might as well use
some of the resources of the World Wide Web to find ways to get in
shape.(Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED. (l, f)
</P>
<P>
   GEEWAX-COLUMN _ ATLANTA _ While hundreds of thousands of
Americans continue to work in the auto industry, their role has
diminished dramatically. The rest of the U.S. economy has grown so
mightily that what's good for GM and its workers no longer matters
very much. (Geewax, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED. (k, f)
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ ATLANTA _ Here's a familiar worry, one that blooms
anew with each generation: Nobody teaches the kids about money
these days. Here's an all-purpose answer, renewable for each
generation of new parents: We have to do it ourselves. (Ezell,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   HOLSENDOLPH-COLUMN _ ATLANTA _ When BellSouth announced that it
is offering something fresh, television over the air to the tune of
some 160 channels, the news created an instant buzz. Lots of folks
out there were saying, I don't know what this wireless television
is, but whatever it is, I want to give it a chance. Anybody but
cable! (Holsendolph, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CONSUMERWATCH _ ATLANTA _ This year's college graduates, thanks
to a strong economy, are enjoying increased job offers with good
salaries -- but many graduates will soon encounter something they
won't like: repaying college loans. (Tharpe, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
