elevated them. (Stoda, Palm Beach Post) MOVED. (s)
</P>
<P>
   HOCKEY-NOTES _ DETROIT _ The first games of the Stanley Cup
finals at Joe Louis Arena marked a homecoming of sorts for
Washington's Adam Oates. Oates, 35, was drafted as a free agent by
Detroit out of Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute (R.P.I.) in Troy,
N.Y., in June 1985 and played four seasons with the Red Wings
before being traded to St. Louis. ``I have some great memories,''
Oates said. (Biggane, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL-SUPERSTITIONS _ Not all baseball superstitions are as
obvious as the Florida Marlins' high black socks. Most of them, you
don't even notice. (Graziano, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MAYNARD-TRUDEAU _ Maynard Trudeau scored a basketful of money at
the NBA Finals. A quarter of a million dollars, that's what they
said. So what exactly has changed in the life of Palm Beach
County's most sudden sports celebrity? ``Nothing,'' says Maynard.
(George, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   GEORGE-COLUMN _ The startling revelation that major league
baseball is in no real danger of petering out in South Florida
actually came to me while team owners gathered last week in
Seattle. (George, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
