<HEADLINE>
AIRY AND COOL CROCHET  
 (JT) 
</HEADLINE>
   By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Crocheted clothing and accessories, airy and
cool-looking for summer, are part of fashion's move away from harsh
minimalism.
</P>
<P>
   Saks Fifth Avenue has a long taupe crocheted dress with its own
slip by Laundry ($185); a white spaghetti-strap dress over a slip
by Mica ($145); a white tank top by Parallel ($74), and an aqua
cardigan by NKL ($90).
</P>
<P>
   Lord &AMP; Taylor has crocheted handbags ($30 to $45); gloves ($15);
soft hats in a range of colors ($17), and fringed scarves ($24).
</P>
<P>
   Benetton, 597 Fifth Avenue (48th Street), is offering crocheted
halters in solids or stripes ($32 to $44).
</P>
<P>
   Henri Bendel has crocheted bags by Gunmarie Nillson ($118) and
Carrie Forbes ($168).
</P>
<P>
   Bergdorf Goodman has a long-sleeved white pullover sweater by
Philosophy di Alberta Ferretti ($270); a V-neck burgundy pullover
($420) and skirt ($315) by Alessandro Dell'Acqua; a silk tank-style
sweater by Tse ($255), and a sleeveless white pullover by John
Galliano ($410).
</P>
<P>
