 &HT;    Beach Boy back with brand new album
 &HT;    By Russ DeVault
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Due at retail stores today is ``Imagination,'' the first album
of mostly new material in 10 years from Beach Boy Brian Wilson,
who'll celebrate his 56th birthday Saturday. He co-produced and
worked on some songs with Jimmy Buffett, Carole Bayer Sager and
J.D. Southern. It's got the Beach Boys' smooth pop sound of summer
and some tracks have as many as 64 layers of vocals.
</P>
<P>
   -- Suzy Bogguss, ``Nobody Love, Nobody Gets Hurt'' (Capitol).
Grade: A.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Dr. Doolittle'' soundtrack (Atlantic). R&AMP;B artist Aaliyah's
``Are You That Somebody'' is stand-out single. Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Queen Latifah,'' Order in the Court'' (Motown). Grade: B-.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The X-Files: The Album'' compilation (Elektra). Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   -- Van Morrison, ``The Philosopher's Stone'' (Polydor/A&AMP;M).
Double-CD compilation of mostly unreleased tunes from 1971-'88
includes collaborations with Jackie De Shannon, the Chieftains and
guitarist Ronnie Montrose.
</P>
