<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-15 19:26 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0281 &Cx1f; taf-z
s t &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TRAVEL-SUNVALLEY-3RDT     06-15 0787
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRAVEL-SUNVALLEY-3RDTAKE-$ADV21-NYT </SLUG>
  
 UNDATED: 65,000 books.  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Ketchum's downtown, no more than about 10 square blocks, is
lined with restaurants, shops and real estate agencies. ``They used
to take gold bullion out of here, and now they're busy bringing it
back,'' my husband said.
</P>
<P>
   But for all the area's delights (including our favorite shop,
Iconoclast Used Books, an old house at 100 First Avenue that had
books packed into every room, including science fiction and humor
collections in the bathroom), it was still the skating that made
our vacation special. One morning, I looked up from navigating my
way around the rink to find Nancy Kerrigan, dressed in shorts and a
sweatshirt, standing off to the side quietly watching the skaters.
</P>
<P>
   In a few minutes, people would recognize her and young girls
would flock for her autograph. But meanwhile, it was possible to
indulge in the momentary fantasy that Nancy Kerrigan was actually
watching me skate.
</P>
<P>
   And it occurred to me: There are any number of places in the
world where you can watch an Olympic champion skate, but in how
many other places could you look up and find one watching you? &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   GETTING THERE: Sun Valley is not really near any major city. We
flew into Salt Lake City, rented a car and drove the nearly 300
miles in about five and a half hours. This drive offers mountain
desert scenery, and a stop at Shoshone Falls on the Snake River in
Twin Falls, Idaho, a spectacular waterfall that is higher than
Niagara.
</P>
<P>
   Another gateway is Boise, about three hours away. A van service
started up a few months ago, making one round trip a day between
the Boise Airport and Sun Valley for $49 each way. Call Sun Valley
Express, (800) 634-6539. There are also commuter flights from Salt
Lake City to Hailey, Idaho, about 10 miles from Sun Valley.
</P>
<P>
   WHERE TO STAY: You can book all resort accommodations through
the Sun Valley Resort, (800) 786-8259. Summer rates at Sun Valley
Inn range from $114 a night for a standard room to $399 for a
three-bedroom apartment. At the larger Sun Valley Lodge, rates are
$139 to $379. No meals are included.
</P>
<P>
   We had a well-furnished, two-bedroom apartment in the resort's
Snow Creek condominium, a short walk from the rink. Rates there and
at Cottonwood, across the street from the rink, start at $209 a
night; no weekly discounts.
</P>
<P>
   Several real estate agencies represent owners of individual
condominiums. The Sun Valley-Ketchum Chamber of Commerce, P.O. Box
2420, Sun Valley, Idaho 83353, keeps a list of rental agents, and
has information about nightly accommodations in Ketchum. Call (800)
634-3347, or see www.visit sunvalley.com.
</P>
<P>
   The Sun Valley Resort maintains a web site, www.sunvalley.com,
and I found useful, information at a commercial site unaffiliated
with the resort, www.svguide.com.
</P>
<P>
   WHERE TO EAT: Have lunch at Sun Valley Lodge's patio restaurant,
Gretchen's, and enjoy the view of the outdoor rink, especially late
in the week, when the pros practice their routines for the Saturday
show. Open 7 a.m. to 10 p.m. Lunch for two with a glass of wine is
about $25; (208) 622-2144.
</P>
<P>
   People go for the steaks and the scene to the Pioneer Saloon,
308 North Main Street, (208) 726-3139, which we found a bit
overwhelmed by its own popularity. Dinner for two with a drink:
about $40.
</P>
<P>
   We had elegant meals at Evergreen Bistro, First Avenue and River
Street, which is open nightly from 6:30. Game dishes are a
specialty, with dinner for two with wine costing about $100; (208)
726-3888.
</P>
<P>
   The list of good Mexican restaurants includes Desperado's,
Fourth Avenue and Washington Street. Dinner entrees run $6 to $9.
Lunch and dinner; (208) 726-3068.
</P>
<P>
   At the Buffalo Cafe, 320 East Avenue E, (208) 726-9795, I had a
_ what else? _ buffalo burger ($7) under the baleful eye of a
mounted buffalo head.
</P>
<P>
   We would gladly return to Chapala, a Mexican place at 502 North
Main Street, Hailey. Open daily 11 a.m. to 10 p.m.; entrees are
$3.99 to 12.50; (208) 788-5065.
</P>
<P>
   North of Ketchum on Route 75, Galena Lodge has an inviting menu,
featuring lamb, beef and salmon. The restaurant is open for lunch
Monday through Saturday, dinner Thursday through Saturday, and
Sunday brunch. Dinner for two with wine is about $45; (208)
726-4010.
</P>
<P>
   FIGURE SKATING: Call the Sun Valley Skating Center, (208)
622-2192, for the school's brochure and reservation form. Ice time
for all 50-minute practice sessions and lessons must be reserved in
weeklong blocks and payment made with the reservation.
</P>
<P>
   The cost is up to $40 for a private 25-minute lesson. Public
sessions last an hour and a half and cost $7.75 and $6.75 for ages
12 and under. Skate rentals are $3.
</P>
</TEXT>
