<SLUG> BC-HKN-STANLEY-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GOALIE OSGOOD HOLDS THE KEY TO DETROIT SWEEP 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By NANCY L. MARRAPESE  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ They go to the movies all the time.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've seen a lot of bad movies,'' confessed Detroit backup
goaltender Kevin Hodson, who attends the flicks with starting
netminder Chris Osgood.
</P>
<P>
   One of the more recent releases the two took in was
``Godzilla.'' Coincidentally, that's the nickname of Washington
goaltender Olaf Kolzig. To this point in the Stanley Cup playoffs,
Kolzig has received most of the ink and attention, while Osgood has
been viewed more as a cog in the wheel of a very powerful Red Wings
team. But Tuesday night, Osgood will be in the position of leading
his club to the Stanley Cup if Detroit can complete the four-game
sweep at the MCI Center.
</P>
<P>
   ``Kolzig is a great goalie,'' said Hodson. ``He hadn't really
done much up to this point, but I think this year he's really
emerged as the No. 1 goalie and deservedly so. He's got a name like
Godzilla, it's a catchy nickname and people like it. Ozzie's kind
of quiet, with a more laidback demeanor, more so than Kolzig is.
</P>
<P>
   ``In some ways I think it helps. All the hype before was on
(Dallas goalie Eddie) Belfour, that Eddie the Eagle was going to
fly high and all these different things. Nothing was said about
Chris. I think one of the great advantages for him as an athlete
and as a goalie is maybe teams take him a little bit lightly or
really don't respect him as much as they should.''
</P>
<P>
   Osgood, who was backup to Mike Vernon last year when the Wings
captured the Cup, goes into Tuesday night with a 15-6 record, 2.17
goals against average, and .916 save percentage in the playoffs.
Kolzig is 12-8, with a 1.86 GAA and .943 save percentage.
</P>
<P>
   As good as Osgood is, he has been considered suspect at times
because of the long-range goals he's given up. Most notably, he
gave up one to Jeremy Roenick from the blue line in the Phoenix
series. But he won the next three games to end it. In the second
round, he gave up a center-ice goal to St. Louis defenseman Al
MacInnis with less than a minute left to send the game into
overtime _ but Osgood went on to win again. Against Dallas, Jamie
Langenbrunner scored from 90 feet to win Game 5 in overtime, but
Osgood shut out the Stars to end the series in Game 6.
</P>
<P>
   When Osgood has been brilliant, often he explains it away by
saying he has a great team in front of him. When he gives up the
odd suspect goal, he's considered a not-ready-for-prime-time
player.
</P>
<P>
   ``The funny thing is, people say Grant Fuhr is a great goalie
and he ended up winning five Cups but the Edmonton teams he played
in front of were dynasties,'' said Hodson. ``Any time you win the
Stanley Cup, you have to have a great team in front of you. That's
just a fact.
</P>
<P>
   ``I kind of laugh at that when people say these guys are good
because of the team in front of him. The team is good because the
goaltending provides a consistency and confidence in his teammates.
Yeah, there's talent on this team and yeah, you should be
successful most years, but you need good goaltending to keep you in
there and Chris has done that, day in and day out.''
</P>
<P>
   Osgood is 25 years old but looks much younger. His blond hair,
blue eyes, and slight frame belie his deep-seated competitive
spirit. He feels, as many others do, that he finally could banish
all the doubters with one more victory.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't take away anything from what happened last year,'' he
said. ``I enjoyed everything about last year, the experience and
winning. Obviously when you play more, it means a little more. I
didn't enjoy not playing (last year) but I accepted it and had a
great time winning the Cup last year but it would be a little more
gratifying this year.''
</P>
<P>
   This ending could be like the one the real Godzilla meets. In
the movie, the big guy gets it in the end. If the script stays the
same here, Osgood will slay all the monsters, too.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
