<SLUG> BC-NJ-WHITMAN-DAUGHTER-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHITMAN'S DAUGHTER CITED FOR LITTERING 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   TRENTON, N.J. _ Kate Whitman, the 21-year-old daughter of Gov.
Christie Whitman, was issued a citation for littering in Bethlehem,
Pa., over the weekend after tossing a beer can in front of a police
officer.
</P>
<P>
   Whitman said that her daughter was visiting friends at Lehigh
University and seemed ``to have had a lapse of judgment.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I have discussed the matter with my daughter and, like any
other parent, I am concerned about the littering charge and Kate's
alleged behavior,'' Whitman said.
</P>
<P>
   Kate Whitman, who lives with her parents in Oldwick, was walking
down a street with three friends at 1:30 a.m. on Saturday when a
police officer stopped her and told her to get rid of a beer can
that she was holding, The Associated Press reported.
</P>
<P>
   The police officer left, but later returned to find Ms. Whitman
with the beer can still in her hand. After she tossed it on the
ground, the police officer issued a citation and she was
handcuffed, the A.P. said.
</P>
<P>
   Whitman said that her daughter had been respectful to the police
officer, but was handcuffed after she had questioned why she was
being ordered into the back seat of the police cruiser.
</P>
<P>
   ``That was the wrong thing to do,'' Mrs. Whitman said. ``She
questioned him as only my daughter can.''
</P>
<P>
   Kate Whitman faces a fine of $50 to $300. ``She will pay
whatever fine is imposed,'' Whitman said. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
