<SLUG> BC-PUBLIC-LIVES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PUBLIC LIVES 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 By JAMES BARRON    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   CONNUBIAL BLISS
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Ethan Hawke was playing the part of the solicitous
husband when he and Uma Thurman, his wife of six weeks who is seven
months pregnant, arrived for a workout at a Greenwich Village gym
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was making a big deal about getting her set up on the
treadmill,'' said another member of the New York Sports Club who
was exercising nearby. ``Then she started on the treadmill, and he
was running around trying to get two treadmills together. While he
was gone, she stumbled and almost fell.''
</P>
<P>
   Once he was back, there was the matter of how fast she was
exercising. ``She was just walking on the treadmill,'' the man
said, ``and at one point she started to jog a bit, and he got
concerned and said something like, `Be careful, you don't want to
go too hard.' She said, `I didn't turn the speed up, but walking so
fast was hurting my legs.' He said, `It's easier to go a long way
at a slower speed, and there are not many women in here who are
carrying a baby, so you're not competing with anybody.' And she
wore her sunglasses the whole time, which if you're trying not to
attract attention is not the way to do it.''
</P>
<P>
   Nor is having a husband who sounds as if he is trying to justify
his decision to marry. ``He was saying that he was talking to a
friend of his about getting married and the friend got upset and
said, `Why would you do that? No reason to,''' the man said. But
Hawke told Miss Thurman that he had replied that while marriage is
not for everybody, it is right for some people.
</P>
<P>
   __
</P>
<P>
   THE QUEEN MOTHER SETS A RECORD
</P>
<P>
   It took her 97 years and 315 days, but Queen Elizabeth the queen
mother has finally clinched a place in British history. On Sunday,
she became the oldest royal ever.
</P>
<P>
   The mother of Queen Elizabeth II and the widow of King George
VI, she passed the record held by Queen Victoria's granddaughter,
Princess Alice, who died on Jan. 3, 1981. The queen mother will
celebrate her 98th birthday on Aug. 4.
</P>
<P>
   ``It is difficult to say it categorically, but I cannot find any
British royal from our records who has lived longer than the queen
mother,'' Harold Brooks-Baker, director of Burke's Peerage, told
The Express in London.
</P>
<P>
   __
</P>
<P>
   JUST ANOTHER FACE IN THE CROWD
</P>
<P>
   Millions of television viewers could probably pick Matt Lauer
out of a lineup of hosts, but at Nick and Toni's, a restaurant in
East Hampton, N.Y., he's just another customer.
</P>
<P>
   ``The hostess called him Eric instead of Matt,'' said a man who
works for the restaurant, ``and took him to the wrong table.''
</P>
<P>
   The table the hostess was heading toward had not been set, so
she turned and led Lauer and his fiancee, Annette Roque, to the
table they were supposed to have had all along, right next to one
occupied by Jellybean Benitez, the record producer who has worked
with Madonna, Sting, Whitney Houston and such Latin artists as
Ruben Blades.
</P>
<P>
   __
</P>
<P>
   TARANTINO LAWYER REBUTS ACCUSATION
</P>
<P>
   A postscript on Quentin Tarantino, who was arrested last week on
a charge of assaulting Leila Mwangi, a customer in an East Village
restaurant last month: Tarantino's lawyer, Paul F. Callan, is
denying the charge, calling it ``a form of celebrity stalking of
the worst kind'' and accusing Ms. Mwangi of pressing it ``to
buttress her allegations'' in a $15 million civil suit she is
filing against Tarantino (which Callan called ``equally
meritless''). Callan is also disputing the police account of the
incident. ``Ms. Mwangi was not involved in any discussions with Mr.
Tarantino about the portrayal of black people in his films,''
Callan said. ``Mr. Tarantino had prior to the incident criticized
racism in Hollywood in the making of various casting decisions.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
